        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="NQuZShNWxpy8CxApDY1Y-243" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;The Kernel Trick allows SVM to create non-linear decision boundaries by computing inner products in a high-dimensional feature space without explicitly performing the transformation&amp;nbsp;`\phi(\mathbf{x})`:$$ K(\mathbf{x}_i, \mathbf{x}_j) = \langle\phi(\mathbf{x}_i), \phi(\mathbf{x}_j)\rangle$$&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;hachureGap=4;fontFamily=Mali;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#F9EBFF;strokeColor=#9673a6;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;labelBorderColor=none;textShadow=0;labelBackgroundColor=none;align=left;spacing=5;verticalAlign=middle;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DMali;arcSize=11;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="60" y="2420" width="532" height="95" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
